---
// cron-round-trip — Chapter 066 Lesson 2 ("Vercel Cron as the schedule default").
//
// The lesson's topology in one glance: a cron is NOT magic — it's an external
// scheduler making a timed HTTP GET to a path you own, whose handler runs as one
// ordinary serverless invocation and returns. Fixing this model first makes every
// later property (it's a public URL, it's bounded by maxDuration, it can be hit
// twice) follow mechanically.
//
//   Vercel Scheduler ──[0 * * * *]──▶ GET /api/cron/sweep-trials
//     (clock glyph)        the cadence       (a request line)
//   GET … ──[Authorization: Bearer CRON_SECRET]──▶ Route handler
//              the secret rides on every request      one invocation → returns
//
// Built with <ArrowDiagram> (LeaderLine) because each box is custom HTML — a
// glyph + title + sub-label, and a monospace request line — that D2/Mermaid
// plain-label boxes wouldn't carry. The auth-header label is long, so it sits
// ABOVE the wire; the short cadence label sits above its own gap, Y-staggered so
// the two badges never collide at the widest desktop width.
//
// The arrows are positioned from document.body, so the wrapping <Figure> MUST be
// expandable={false}: relocating the body into the lightbox breaks leader lines.
//
// Chrome is theme-aware (Starlight gray/white vars flip light/dark). The two
// accents (#0ea5e9 scheduler-blue for the cadence wire, #f97316 secret-orange for
// the auth wire) are used as-is in both themes — mid-tones that read on either
// background. A margin:0 reset defeats Starlight's injected prose margins.

import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';

import Figure from '../../../figures/Figure.astro';
import ArrowDiagram from '../../../figures/ArrowDiagram.astro';

// Mid-tone accents reused verbatim in light + dark.
const CADENCE_BLUE = '#0ea5e9'; // the clock wire — Vercel fires on a cadence
const SECRET_ORANGE = '#f97316'; // the secret rides on every request

const arrows = [
	// The scheduler fires on its cadence — the cron expression labels the wire.
	{
		from: 'cron-scheduler',
		to: 'cron-get',
		label: '0 * * * *',
		color: CADENCE_BLUE,
		startSocket: 'right',
		endSocket: 'left',
		startSocketGravity: [70, 0],
		endSocketGravity: [-70, 0],
		labelOffset: [0, -34],
	},
	// The request reaches your route handler — Vercel attaches the bearer secret
	// to every cron request. Long label, lifted further above to clear the curve.
	{
		from: 'cron-get',
		to: 'cron-handler',
		label: 'Authorization: Bearer CRON_SECRET',
		color: SECRET_ORANGE,
		startSocket: 'right',
		endSocket: 'left',
		startSocketGravity: [70, 0],
		endSocketGravity: [-70, 0],
		labelOffset: [0, -44],
	},
];
---

<Figure expandable={false}>
	<ArrowDiagram arrows={arrows}>
		<div class="crt not-content">
			{/* The external scheduler — a clock, because all it does is fire on time. */}
			<div class="crt-box crt-box--scheduler" id="cron-scheduler">
				<span class="crt-glyph" aria-hidden="true">
					<Icon name="lucide:clock" />
				</span>
				<span class="crt-title">Vercel Scheduler</span>
				<span class="crt-sub">fires on a cadence</span>
			</div>

			{/* The wire payload — a plain HTTP GET to a path you own. */}
			<div class="crt-box crt-box--get" id="cron-get">
				<span class="crt-req">
					<span class="crt-verb">GET</span>
					<span class="crt-path">/api/cron/sweep-trials</span>
				</span>
				<span class="crt-sub crt-sub--get">a public path you own</span>
			</div>

			{/* The handler — one ordinary serverless invocation, then it returns. */}
			<div class="crt-box crt-box--handler" id="cron-handler">
				<span class="crt-title">Route handler</span>
				<span class="crt-sub">one invocation → returns</span>
			</div>
		</div>
	</ArrowDiagram>
	<Fragment slot="caption">
		A cron is an external scheduler making a timed <code>GET</code> to a public
		path you own. The handler runs as a normal invocation — and the secret rides
		along on every request.
	</Fragment>
</Figure>

<style>
	.crt {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: nowrap;
		align-items: stretch;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 96px;
		margin: 0;
		/* Extra top padding reserves room for the lifted labels above the wires. */
		padding: 30px 4px 14px;
		font-family:
			ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
	}

	.crt-box {
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 4px;
		flex: 0 1 auto;
		padding: 12px 16px;
		border-radius: 10px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, transparent);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* The scheduler box leads with the clock accent. */
	.crt-box--scheduler {
		border-color: color-mix(in srgb, #0ea5e9 45%, var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1));
	}

	/* The handler box is the destination — a soft accent ring marks "the work". */
	.crt-box--handler {
		border-color: var(--sl-color-gray-4, #94a3b8);
	}

	.crt-glyph {
		display: inline-flex;
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		line-height: 1;
		color: #0ea5e9;
		margin: 0 0 1px;
	}

	.crt-title {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.2;
		white-space: nowrap;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* The middle box renders as a request line: monospace path + a verb pill. */
	.crt-req {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: baseline;
		gap: 7px;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.crt-verb {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 0.66rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		line-height: 1;
		padding: 3px 6px;
		border-radius: 5px;
		color: #fff;
		background: #0ea5e9;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.crt-path {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 0.84rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.2;
		white-space: nowrap;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.crt-sub {
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		line-height: 1.2;
		white-space: nowrap;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.crt-sub--get {
		color: color-mix(in srgb, #f97316 78%, var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b));
	}

	/* Narrow viewports: stack the three boxes; the right→left sockets degrade to
	   vertical arcs between stacked boxes — readable, and the labels still float in
	   the gaps. */
	@media (max-width: 680px) {
		.crt {
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 58px;
			padding-top: 14px;
		}
		.crt-box {
			width: min(20rem, 100%);
		}
	}
</style>
